HEADWORD: Ectostosis
<hw>Ec`tos*to"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Ect-</er>, and <er>Ostosis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A
process of bone formation in which ossification takes place in the
perichondrium and either surrounds or gradually replaces the
cartilage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ectozoic</ent>⟦br⟧
